# CELLIX Backend Core Rule

- Treat `docs/CELLIX_TECHNICAL_DOCUMENTATION.md` (repo root) as the source-of-truth design doc. Legacy drafts under `cellix_backend/docs/` are superseded pointers only.
- Keep NestJS modular under `src/` (`config`, `database`, `logging`, `excel-ai`, `agents`, `audit`, `formula`, `virtual`, `domain-tools`, `sheets`, `llm`, `health`). `app.module.ts` is wiring only.
- Prefer deterministic-first routing: LlmRouter shortcuts / Tier 0 → Tier 1 → Tier 2 → Tier 3 (Planner→Executor→Verifier) gated by `ENABLE_COMPLEXITY_TIERING`.
- Preserve typed SSE conversation contracts (`POST /excel-ai/conversation`) and ChangeSet audit provenance (`sourceRefs` / `exceptionFlags`).
- Executor output: normalize A1 `range` → indices for FORMAT-class actions; do not loosen `sanitizeAction`'s row/col contract.
- Enforce DTO validation and fail-fast `@nestjs/config` + Joi for env keys.
- Treat audit / request / planner logs as append-only and traceable; dual-write file (24h) + Mongo TTL (3d).
- Prefer secure defaults as features land (auth, throttling, helmet); do not invent secrets in the client.
- Optimize for cost/perf: complexity tiers, TOON compression, context cache, avoid unnecessary LLM calls.
- Keep compatibility with current `package.json` scripts (npm); do not change package manager without user approval.
- When adding features, include tests and update `docs/CELLIX_TECHNICAL_DOCUMENTATION.md` / architecture diagrams for new modules/endpoints.
